就是他
That's him. That's the one.

00:53:35.320 --> 00:53:36.480
我是狄金斯
I'm Dekins.

00:53:36.890 --> 00:53:38.520
我在想……
I was thinking...

00:53:39.190 --> 00:53:43.060
为孩子弄个教育基金
about setting up some kind of trust fund for my kids' educations.

00:53:46.970 --> 00:53:48.460
我懂了
I see.

00:53:53.540 --> 00:53:56.510
咱们坐下谈吧
Why don't we have a seat and talk it over.

00:53:59.210 --> 00:54:02.670
老布  有纸笔吗？
Do you have a piece of paper and a pencil?

00:54:14.030 --> 00:54:15.320
谢谢
Thanks.

00:54:16.000 --> 00:54:17.050
那么
So...

00:54:18.830 --> 00:54:20.560
狄金斯先生
Mister Dekins...

00:54:21.400 --> 00:54:23.490
然后安迪说
And then Andy says, "Mr. Dekins...

00:54:23.700 --> 00:54:26.700
“你想让贵公子进哈佛还是耶鲁？”
do you want your sons to go to Harvard or Yale?"

00:54:26.910 --> 00:54:27.960
你少瞎扯
He didn't say that!

00:54:28.310 --> 00:54:30.800
真的  老天为证
As God as my witness!

00:54:31.080 --> 00:54:32.810
他愣了一下
Dekins blinked for a second...

00:54:33.010 --> 00:54:36.310
傻笑出来  后来真跟安迪握手了
then he laughed and actually shook Andy's hand.

00:54:36.580 --> 00:54:38.850
-握你的鸟  -真的握手
-My ass!  -Shook his hand.

00:54:39.090 --> 00:54:41.990
我乐的差点尿出来
I tell you, I near soiled myself!

00:54:42.190 --> 00:54:46.450
若给安迪弄一套西装领带
All he needed was a suit and tie and a jiggly hula gal on his desk...

00:54:46.660 --> 00:54:49.250
他就成了“咨询先生”
he'd have been "Mr. Dufresne," if you please.

00:54:49.460 --> 00:54:51.090
开始交新朋友了  安迪？
Making a few friends?

00:54:52.400 --> 00:54:54.060
也不算“朋友”
I wouldn't say "friends."

00:54:54.270 --> 00:54:58.100
我是精通理财的囚徒
I'm a convicted murderer who provides sound financial planning.

00:54:58.300 --> 00:55:00.640
这种本事很受用
It's a wonderful pet to have.

00:55:00.840 --> 00:55:02.640
起码不用干洗衣工
Got you out of the laundry, though.

00:55:03.180 --> 00:55:05.080
还派得上更大用场
It might do more than that.

00:55:05.310 --> 00:55:08.010
比如扩建图书馆  买新书
How about expanding the library. Get some new books.

00:55:08.210 --> 00:55:10.810
还不如申请张台球桌
If you ask for something, ask for a pool table.

00:55:11.380 --> 00:55:12.370
对
yes.

00:55:12.550 --> 00:55:15.520
你想怎么弄？
How do you expect to do that? I mean...

00:55:15.720 --> 00:55:18.690
我是说  “咨询先生”  你打算怎么弄到新书？
get new books in here, "Mr. Dufresne, if you please."

00:55:19.160 --> 00:55:21.220
找典狱长要钱
I'll ask the warden for funds.

00:55:22.100 --> 00:55:26.360
孩子  我经历了六任典狱长
Son, son, son... Six wardens have been through here in my tenure, and I've learned...

00:55:26.600 --> 00:55:28.900
学到的互古不变的真理就是
one immutable, universal truth:

00:55:29.140 --> 00:55:30.530
给钱是不可能的
Not one born whose asshole...

00:55:30.740 --> 00:55:35.670
他们没一个生来有屁眼
wouldn't pucker up tighter than a snare drum when you ask for funds.

00:55:36.540 --> 00:55:39.440
-预算太少了  -我了解
-The budget's stretched thin as it is.  -I see.

00:55:39.650 --> 00:55:43.080
我可以写信跟州议会要钱
Maybe I could write the state senate and request funds from them.

00:55:43.280 --> 00:55:47.380
监狱领到款只能做三种用途
They have only three ways to spend the taxpayers' money for prisons:

00:55:47.590 --> 00:55:50.020
筑高墙  加牢笼  添警卫
More walls, more bars, more guards.

00:55:50.220 --> 00:55:52.890
我仍请您恩准  一周一信
I'd like to try, with permission. A letter a week.

00:55:53.090 --> 00:55:55.820
-总会有结果  -难说哦
-They can't ignore me forever.  -Sure can.

00:55:56.100 --> 00:55:58.760
想写就写吧
But you write your letters if it makes you happy.

00:55:59.070 --> 00:56:01.660
我一定寄出  行吗？
I'll even mail them for you. How's that?

00:56:03.340 --> 00:56:06.130
安迪开始一周一信
So Andy started writing a letter a week...

00:56:06.340 --> 00:56:07.930
他说话算话
just like he said.

00:56:12.110 --> 00:56:14.740
不过  就像诺顿说的
And like Norton said...

00:56:14.950 --> 00:56:16.440
毫无回音
Andy got no answers.

00:56:24.620 --> 00:56:29.530
次年  他替半数的警卫报税
The following April, he did tax returns for half the guards at Shawshank.

00:56:30.860 --> 00:56:33.130
再过一年  全都找他帮忙
Year after that, he did them all...

00:56:33.370 --> 00:56:35.300
包括典狱长的
including the warden's.

00:56:37.040 --> 00:56:40.490
再过一年  狱际棒球赛
Year after that, they rescheduled the intramural season...

00:56:40.710 --> 00:56:43.140
改在与税季重叠
to coincide with tax season.

00:56:44.710 --> 00:56:49.170
各监狱的警卫都带税单找他
The guards on the opposing teams all remembered to bring their W-2s.

00:56:49.380 --> 00:56:50.710
狱方发枪给你
So Moresby Prison...

00:56:50.920 --> 00:56:53.180
但要你付钱
issued you a gun, but you paid for it.

00:56:53.420 --> 00:56:55.110
连枪套也要我付
Right. The holster too.

00:56:55.320 --> 00:56:57.810
这笔钱可以扣除
That's tax-deductible. You can write that off.

00:56:57.990 --> 00:57:01.020
没错  安迪就像开小作坊
Yes, sir! Andy was a regular cottage industry.

00:57:01.730 --> 00:57:06.220
税季繁忙时  还可请帮手
In fact, it got so busy at tax time, he was allowed a staff.

00:57:06.500 --> 00:57:08.990
请帮我拿一叠表格
Could you hand me a stack of 1040s?

00:57:09.170 --> 00:57:14.000
每年此时我调离工厂  乐到心坎里
Got me out of the wood shop a month out of the year, and that was fine by me.

00:57:15.240 --> 00:57:18.400
至于信  他仍继续寄
And still, he kept sending those letters.

00:57:23.180 --> 00:57:26.210
瑞德  安迪  老布出事了
It's Brooks.

00:57:27.350 --> 00:57:28.840
守着门
Watch the door.

00:57:29.090 --> 00:57:30.420
冷静点  老布
Please, Brooks.

00:57:30.690 --> 00:57:32.490
-冲动个啥  -混帐  退后
-Calm the fuck down.  -Stay back!

00:57:32.930 --> 00:57:35.550
-都退后  -怎么回事？
-Stay back, goddamn it!  -What's going on?

00:57:35.760 --> 00:57:38.320
上一秒好好的  突然亮刀子
One second he's fine, then out come the knives.

00:57:38.530 --> 00:57:40.330
老布  有话好说
We can talk about this, right?

00:57:40.600 --> 00:57:44.330
放屁  没啥可说  我要割断他喉咙
There's nothing to talk about. I'll cut his fucking throat.

00:57:44.600 --> 00:57:46.330
等一下  赫伍哪里不对？
What's he done to you?

00:57:46.540 --> 00:57:48.200
错在他们
It's what they done!

00:57:48.710 --> 00:57:49.970
我别无选择
I got no choice.

00:57:50.440 --> 00:57:52.740
谁都知道你不会伤害他
You won't hurt Heywood. We all know that.

00:57:52.950 --> 00:57:55.440
-对  是吧赫伍？  -没错
-Right, Heywood?  -Sure.

00:57:55.650 --> 00:57:58.980
因为他是朋友  而你明理
He's a friend of yours, and Brooks is a reasonable man.

00:57:59.250 --> 00:58:01.020
-对不对？
Right, guys?

00:58:01.290 --> 00:58:03.810
老布  看着我  放下刀
So put the knife down. Look at me.

00:58:04.060 --> 00:58:06.290
把刀放下
Put the knife down.

00:58:08.230 --> 00:58:10.320
老布  你瞧他的脖子
Look at his neck, for God's sake.

00:58:11.060 --> 00:58:13.400
看看  都流血了
Look at his neck. He's bleeding.

00:58:14.300 --> 00:58:15.790
只有闯祸……
It's the only way...

00:58:15.970 --> 00:58:18.030
才能留在牢里
they'd let me stay.

00:58:18.300 --> 00:58:20.670
怎么可能  别做傻事
This is crazy. You don't want to do this.

00:58:20.910 --> 00:58:22.970
把刀放下
Put it, put it down.

00:58:31.750 --> 00:58:33.240
放松点
Take it easy.

00:58:33.920 --> 00:58:35.480
不会有事的
You'll be all right.

00:58:35.660 --> 00:58:38.150
他没事  我呢？
Him? What about me?

00:58:38.320 --> 00:58:40.720
老疯狗差点割断我喉咙
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!

00:58:40.930 --> 00:58:42.830
你刮胡子不也刀刀见血
You've had worse from shaving.

00:58:43.030 --> 00:58:45.120
你怎么惹毛他的？
What did you do to set him off?

00:58:45.330 --> 00:58:47.560
哪有  我只是来道别
Nothing. I come in here to say farewell.

00:58:48.170 --> 00:58:50.830
上面准他假释了
Ain't you heard? His parole's come through.

00:58:53.040 --> 00:58:55.970
我实在搞不明白
I just don't understand what happened in there.

00:58:56.180 --> 00:58:58.970
这老家伙简直疯了
Old man's crazy as a rat in a tin shithouse.

00:58:59.180 --> 00:59:01.080
赫伍  住口
That's enough out of you.

00:59:01.280 --> 00:59:04.010
-听说你吓的屁滚尿流  -滚你的
-Heard he had you shitting your pants. -Fuck you.

00:59:04.280 --> 00:59:05.480
别斗嘴了
Knock it off.

00:59:06.450 --> 00:59:07.890
老布没疯
Brooks ain't no bug.

00:59:08.320 --> 00:59:09.410
他只是……
he is just...

00:59:11.720 --> 00:59:13.490
体制化了
institutionalized.

00:59:14.860 --> 00:59:16.800
“体制化”？  什么鸟词儿
"Institutionalized," my ass.

00:59:17.000 --> 00:59:20.990
他坐了50年的牢  赫伍  50年呀
The man's been in here 50 years, Heywood, 50 years!

00:59:21.200 --> 00:59:22.930
成了井底之蛙
This is all he knows.

00:59:23.140 --> 00:59:25.430
他念过书
In here, he's an important man...

00:59:25.640 --> 00:59:26.730
在狱中有地位
an educated man.

00:59:27.540 --> 00:59:29.470
出狱就成了废人
Outside, he's nothing.

00:59:30.340 --> 00:59:33.840
双手犯关节炎的囚徒
Just a used-up con with arthritis in both hands.

00:59:34.050 --> 00:59:37.040
想向图书馆借书都会被拒
Probably couldn't get a library card if he tried.

00:59:37.320 --> 00:59:39.050
这样说你懂吗？
You know what I'm trying to say?

00:59:39.320 --> 00:59:42.220
我才不懂你的满嘴屁话
I do believe you're talking out of your ass.

00:59:43.490 --> 00:59:45.720
随你怎么想吧
You believe whatever you want.

00:59:46.330 --> 00:59:48.730
监狱是怪地方
But I tell you these walls are funny.

00:59:50.330 --> 00:59:51.990
起先你恨它
First you hate them.

00:59:53.830 --> 00:59:55.730
然后习惯它
Then you get used to them.

00:59:57.670 --> 00:59:59.660
更久后
Enough time passes...

01:00:00.340 --> 01:00:02.330
你离不开它
you get so you depend on them.

01:00:03.340 --> 01:00:05.540
这就叫“体制化”
That's "institutionalized."

01:00:05.750 --> 01:00:07.040
狗屎
Shit.

01:00:07.250 --> 01:00:10.010
-我才不会呢  -是吗？
-I could never get like that. -Oh, yeah?

01:00:10.880 --> 01:00:13.370
等你呆到老布那把年纪 你就知道了
Wait till you've been here as long as Brooks.

01:00:13.620 --> 01:00:15.180
说的太对了
Goddamn right.

01:00:17.760 --> 01:00:19.690
他们把你送到这里来度日
They send you here for life...

01:00:20.360 --> 01:00:22.690
等于拿走你一生的年华
that's exactly what they take.

01:00:24.430 --> 01:00:26.420
至少是一大部分
Part that counts, anyway.

01:00:34.040 --> 01:00:36.980
杰克  我无法再照顾你
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

01:00:38.140 --> 01:00:39.810
走吧  你自由了
You go on now.

01:00:41.050 --> 01:00:42.540
自由了
You're free.

01:00:43.820 --> 01:00:45.370
自由了
You're free.

01:01:04.400 --> 01:01:06.070
一切顺利  老布
Good luck, Brooksie.

01:01:08.370 --> 01:01:10.430
保重

01:01:44.040 --> 01:01:45.530
“亲爱的牢友：”
Dear fellas:

01:01:45.810 --> 01:01:50.010
“外头的变化快得难以置信。”
I can't believe how fast things move on the outside.

01:01:51.320 --> 01:01:53.980
老头儿  嫌命长吗
Watch it, old-timer! Want to get killed?

01:01:55.220 --> 01:01:58.710
“小时候我只看过一辆汽车，”
I saw an automobile once when I was a kid...

01:01:59.360 --> 01:02:01.790
“如今满街都是，”
but now they're everywhere.

01:02:05.470 --> 01:02:09.770
“整个世界忙成一团。”
The world went and got itself in a big damn hurry.

01:02:25.590 --> 01:02:29.350
“上面安排我”
The parole board got me into this halfway house...

01:02:29.660 --> 01:02:31.320
“到‘中途之家’，”
called "The Brewer"...

01:02:31.520 --> 01:02:32.680
“并在超市”
and a job...

01:02:32.890 --> 01:02:35.860
“当包装员。”
bagging groceries at the Food-Way.

01:02:37.400 --> 01:02:39.830
“工作辛苦，我也卖力，”
It's hard work and I try to keep up...

01:02:40.030 --> 01:02:42.400
“但双手一直犯疼。”
..but my hands hurt most of the time.

01:02:42.700 --> 01:02:44.670
叫他务必用双层袋
Make sure your man double-bags.

01:02:44.870 --> 01:02:46.900
上次差点撑破袋子
Last time, the bottom near came out.

01:02:47.570 --> 01:02:50.510
确定要用双层袋
Make sure you double-bag like the lady says. understand?

01:02:50.710 --> 01:02:52.080
是  没问题
Yes, sir. Surely will.

01:02:52.280 --> 01:02:55.810
“店长不怎么喜欢我。”
I don't think the store manager likes me very much.

01:02:58.820 --> 01:03:03.120
“工作之余我去公园喂鸟，”
Sometimes after work, I go to the park and feed the birds.

01:03:03.560 --> 01:03:05.050
“盼望……”
I keep thinking...

01:03:05.290 --> 01:03:08.620
“杰克来打个招呼，”
Jake might just show up and say hello.

01:03:09.230 --> 01:03:11.220
“但它没出现过。”
But he never does.

01:03:12.430 --> 01:03:17.300
“不管它在何处，我祝它过的好、有新朋友。”
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay and making new friends.

01:03:20.910 --> 01:03:23.640
“我夜间难以入眠，”
I have trouble sleeping at night.

01:03:23.940 --> 01:03:27.210
“做着从高处坠落的噩梦。”
I have bad dreams like I'm falling.

01:03:27.480 --> 01:03:29.710
“从梦中惊醒，”
I wake up scared.

01:03:29.920 --> 01:03:34.150
“有时记不起身在何方。”
Sometimes it takes me a while to remember where I am.

01:03:35.660 --> 01:03:40.560
“也许我该持枪抢劫，好让他们送我回去。”
Maybe I should get a gun and rob the Food-Way so they'd send me home.

01:03:40.860 --> 01:03:45.190
“我可以打死那个店长，当作额外奖励。”
I could shoot the manager while I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.

01:03:46.870 --> 01:03:50.860
“但我老的无法再胡闹了。”
I guess I'm too old for that sort of nonsense anymore.

01:03:51.100 --> 01:03:52.830
“我不喜欢这里，”
I don't like it here.

01:03:53.040 --> 01:03:57.030
“我厌倦成天担惊受怕。”
I'm tired of being afraid all the time. I've decided...

01:03:57.880 --> 01:03:59.540
“于是，我决心不再逗留。”
not to stay.

01:04:10.460 --> 01:04:13.020
“当局不会在乎我，”
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...

01:04:13.230 --> 01:04:16.720
“一个糟老头算什么。”
not for an old crook like me.

01:05:19.190 --> 01:05:23.460
“当局不会在乎我，一个糟老头算什么。”
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss, not for an old crook like me.

01:05:24.500 --> 01:05:28.330
“还有，替我向赫伍道歉，”
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry I put a knife to his throat.

01:05:28.530 --> 01:05:30.870
“别记恨在心。你们的老布”
No hard feelings. Brooks."

01:05:41.350 --> 01:05:43.320
他还不如老死在肖申克好
He should have died in here.

01:05:48.850 --> 01:05:50.250
瞧瞧你干的好事
What the fuck have you done?

01:05:50.460 --> 01:05:53.120
一片混乱
It's a goddamn mess, I'll tell you that.

01:05:58.660 --> 01:06:02.400
-这些是什么？  -你说呢  全是寄给你的
-What's all this?  -You tell me. They're addressed to you.

01:06:03.670 --> 01:06:05.000
看下这个
Take it.

01:06:13.550 --> 01:06:15.040
“杜弗伦先生：”
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:

01:06:16.180 --> 01:06:18.150
“鉴于你再三询问，”
In response to your inquiries...

01:06:18.350 --> 01:06:22.620
“本州特拨款给贵图书馆。”
the state has allocated the enclosed funds for your library project."

01:06:23.390 --> 01:06:25.220
有两百元
This is $ 200.

01:06:25.420 --> 01:06:29.420
“另外，主管单位”
"In addition, the library district has generously responded...

01:06:29.630 --> 01:06:32.190
“特地捐赠旧书及杂物，”
with a donation of used books and sundries.

01:06:32.400 --> 01:06:36.530
“相信可满足阁下需要，就此了结，”
We trust this will fill your needs. We now consider the matter closed.

01:06:36.740 --> 01:06:38.530
“勿再来信。”
Please stop sending us letters."

01:06:38.770 --> 01:06:41.430
典狱长回来前清理干净
Clear all this out before the warden gets back.

01:06:41.670 --> 01:06:42.830
是
Yes, sir.

01:06:47.110 --> 01:06:48.270
干的好  安迪
Good for you, Andy.

01:06:51.250 --> 01:06:52.380
哇！
Wow!

01:06:53.590 --> 01:06:55.520
只写了六年
It only took six years.

01:06:57.090 --> 01:06:59.820
现在起我一周两封
From now on, I'll write two letters a week instead of one.

01:07:00.030 --> 01:07:03.360
你真够固执的  听队长的话
I believe you're crazy enough.  Get this stuff out...

01:07:03.630 --> 01:07:06.060
把东西清干净  我去解大便
like he said. I've got to pinch a loaf.

01:07:06.270 --> 01:07:07.760
别让我出来
When I come back...

01:07:07.930 --> 01:07:09.700
再看到这些
this is all gone, all right?

01:07:58.450 --> 01:07:59.850
安迪  什么声音？
Do you hear that?

01:09:08.590 --> 01:09:09.750
杜弗伦
Dufresne!

01:09:12.290 --> 01:09:13.820
安迪  放我出去！
Andy, let me out!

01:09:16.800 --> 01:09:18.160
安迪！
Andy!

01:09:20.700 --> 01:09:25.640
到现在我还搞不懂她们唱什么
I have no idea to this day what those two Italian ladies were singing about.

01:09:25.940 --> 01:09:28.170
其实我也不想弄懂
Truth is, I don't want to know.

01:09:28.370 --> 01:09:30.870
此时无言胜有言
Some things are best left unsaid.

01:09:34.450 --> 01:09:37.180
她们唱出
I like to think it was something so beautiful...

01:09:37.380 --> 01:09:39.510
难以言传的美
it can't be expressed in words...

01:09:39.720 --> 01:09:42.620
美得令你心碎
and makes your heart ache because of it.

01:09:44.290 --> 01:09:46.780
歌声直窜云端
I tell you, those voices soared...

01:09:47.060 --> 01:09:51.360
超越失意囚徒的梦想
higher and farther than anybody in a gray place dares to dream.

01:09:51.560 --> 01:09:54.930
宛如小鸟飞入牢房
It was like a beautiful bird flapped into our drab cage...

01:09:55.130 --> 01:09:57.900
使石墙消失无踪
and made those walls dissolve away.

01:09:58.340 --> 01:10:00.530
就在这一瞬间
And for the briefest of moments...

01:10:00.740 --> 01:10:03.730
肖申克众囚仿佛重获自由
every last man at Shawshank felt free.

01:10:06.310 --> 01:10:08.970
典狱长可发飚了
It pissed the warden off something awful.

01:10:10.280 --> 01:10:11.270
开门
Open the door.

01:10:14.190 --> 01:10:15.950
开门
Open it up!

01:10:17.260 --> 01:10:19.990
杜弗伦  开门
Dufresne, open this door!

01:10:21.330 --> 01:10:22.520
关掉
Turn that off!

01:10:29.600 --> 01:10:32.040
我警告你  关掉
I am warning you. Turn that off!

01:10:46.150 --> 01:10:48.120
杜弗伦
Dufresne!

01:10:49.790 --> 01:10:51.310
敬酒不吃吃罚酒
You're mine now.

01:10:58.760 --> 01:11:02.000
安迪被关禁闭两周
Andy got two weeks in the hole for that little stunt.

01:11:02.200 --> 01:11:03.790
站起来
On your feet.

01:11:04.970 --> 01:11:07.370
-看谁来了  -大指挥家
-Hey, look who's here.  -Maestro!

01:11:09.140 --> 01:11:12.800
你没别的可放吗？  比如汉克·威廉斯的歌？
You couldn't play something good, huh? Like Hank Williams?

01:11:13.150 --> 01:11:15.940
没等接受点歌  他们就破门而入了
They broke the door down before I could take requests.

01:11:16.150 --> 01:11:19.280
-关两周值得吗？  -我最舒服的两周
-Was it worth two weeks?  -Easiest time I ever did.

01:11:19.490 --> 01:11:23.680
-屁话  关小号最难熬了  -在里面度日如年
-No such thing as easy time in the hole. -A week in the hole is like a year.

01:11:23.890 --> 01:11:27.190
-半点不假  -有莫札特陪我
-Damn straight.  -I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

01:11:27.390 --> 01:11:30.360
他们准你带留声机？
So they let you tote that record player down there, huh?

01:11:32.800 --> 01:11:34.160
在脑中
It was in here.

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:36.230
在心底
In here.

01:11:37.370 --> 01:11:39.460
音乐之美
That's the beauty of music.

01:11:39.670 --> 01:11:42.000
是夺不走的
They can't get that from you.

01:11:45.540 --> 01:11:47.910
你没体会过吗？
Haven't you ever felt that way about music?

01:11:49.720 --> 01:11:52.840
我年轻时吹过口琴
Well, I played a mean harmonica as a younger man.

01:11:53.890 --> 01:11:55.580
后来没兴致了
Lost interest in it, though.

01:11:55.790 --> 01:11:57.380
在牢里也没意义
Didn't make much sense in here.

01:11:57.720 --> 01:11:59.710
就是在这里才有意义
Here's where it makes the most sense.

01:12:00.260 --> 01:12:02.320
有音乐才不会忘记
You need it so you don't forget.

01:12:02.900 --> 01:12:04.090
忘记什么？
Forget?

01:12:04.460 --> 01:12:07.560
世上
Forget that there are...

01:12:07.770 --> 01:12:09.200
有些地方
places...

01:12:09.700 --> 01:12:13.540
是石墙围不住的
in the world that aren't made out of stone.

01:12:14.540 --> 01:12:16.030
在人的
There's something...

01:12:16.380 --> 01:12:17.770
内心深处
inside...

01:12:18.040 --> 01:12:20.010
有他们找不到
that they can't get to...

01:12:20.210 --> 01:12:21.580
拿不走的东西
that they can't touch.

01:12:22.110 --> 01:12:23.550
完全属于你自己的东西
That's yours.

01:12:25.080 --> 01:12:26.680
你指什么？
What are you talking about?

01:12:27.720 --> 01:12:28.950
希望
Hope.

01:12:30.020 --> 01:12:31.350
希望
Hope.

01:12:33.290 --> 01:12:35.280
朋友  我告诉你
Let me tell you something, my friend.

01:12:36.100 --> 01:12:38.390
有希望才危险
Hope is a dangerous thing.

01:12:39.570 --> 01:12:41.900
希望能把人逼疯
Hope can drive a man insane.

01:12:42.630 --> 01:12:44.760
在这里  希望毫无用处
It's got no use on the inside.

01:12:44.970 --> 01:12:47.170
你最好认命
You'd better get used to that idea.

01:12:49.680 --> 01:12:51.170
要像老布一样吗？
Like Brooks did?

01:13:16.540 --> 01:13:17.520
坐下
Sit down.

01:13:22.880 --> 01:13:26.170
根据你的材料 你的终身监禁已经服满30年
Says here that you've served 30 years of a life sentence.

01:13:27.350 --> 01:13:29.410
你改过自新了吗？
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

01:13:29.620 --> 01:13:30.840
是的
Oh, yes, sir.

01:13:32.120 --> 01:13:33.450
我真的已经变好了
Without a doubt.

01:13:34.620 --> 01:13:37.020
我完全洗心革面了
I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

01:13:39.020 --> 01:13:40.960
我不会再危害社会
No danger to society here.

01:13:41.490 --> 01:13:43.020
我向上帝发誓
God's honest truth.

01:13:45.600 --> 01:13:47.690
我绝对改过自新了
Absolutely rehabilitated.

01:13:57.740 --> 01:13:59.070
30年了
Thirty years.

01:14:01.050 --> 01:14:02.950
老天  真不知该说什么？
Jesus, when you say it like that...

01:14:03.820 --> 01:14:05.610
这些日子怎么熬过来的
You wonder where it went.

01:14:08.050 --> 01:14:10.210
我连前十年都不记得了
I wonder where 10 years went.

01:14:15.190 --> 01:14:16.220
拿去
Here.

01:14:16.660 --> 01:14:19.390
假释被拒的礼物
A little parole rejection present.

01:14:20.670 --> 01:14:22.360
打开看看
Go ahead and open it.

01:14:23.470 --> 01:14:25.490
别介意我找你同行买
Went through one of your competitors.

01:14:25.700 --> 01:14:28.830
我只想给你一个惊喜
I hope you don't mind. I wanted it to be a surprise.

01:14:38.880 --> 01:14:40.370
漂亮极了
It's very pretty.

01:14:42.090 --> 01:14:43.280
谢谢
Thank you.

01:14:45.860 --> 01:14:47.350
你不吹吗？
You going to play it?

01:14:51.900 --> 01:14:53.160
不
No.

01:14:56.770 --> 01:14:58.170
不是时候
Not right now.

01:15:15.850 --> 01:15:16.950
进牢
Roll in!

01:15:53.160 --> 01:15:54.390
熄灯
Lights out!

01:16:28.990 --> 01:16:31.120
安迪言出必行
Andy was as good as his word.

01:16:31.500 --> 01:16:34.260
每周写两封信
He wrote two letters a week instead of one.

01:16:36.340 --> 01:16:40.430
59年  州议会终于明白
In 1959, the state senate finally clued in to the fact...

01:16:40.670 --> 01:16:43.800
两百元无法打发安迪
they couldn't buy him off with just a $ 200 check.

01:16:44.010 --> 01:16:48.310
当局决定每年拨款五百美元
Appropriations Committee voted an annual payment of $500...

01:16:48.510 --> 01:16:50.410
好让安迪封笔
just to shut him up.

01:16:50.620 --> 01:16:53.610
你想像不到他的能耐
And you'd be amazed how far Andy could stretch it.

01:16:53.820 --> 01:16:56.750
他接洽读书会  慈善团体
He made deals with book clubs, charity groups.

01:16:56.960 --> 01:16:59.720
他论斤买入旧书
He bought remaindered books by the pound...

01:17:00.230 --> 01:17:01.750
《金银岛》
"Treasure Island".

01:17:02.290 --> 01:17:03.630
罗伯特·路易斯
Robert Louis...

01:17:03.830 --> 01:17:04.850
史蒂文森
Stevenson.

01:17:05.060 --> 01:17:06.430
冒险小说类
Fiction, adventure.

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:10.020
下一本
What's next?

01:17:10.240 --> 01:17:13.300
汽车维修
I got here Auto Repair...

01:17:14.040 --> 01:17:15.200
肥皂雕刻
and Soap Carving.

01:17:15.410 --> 01:17:18.640
专业技术及嗜好  教育类  在你后面
Trade skills and hobbies. Under "Educational," behind you.

01:17:18.840 --> 01:17:20.710
基堵山恩仇记
Count of Monte Crisco.

01:17:21.180 --> 01:17:23.480
基督山  饭桶
That's "Cristo," you dumb shit.

01:17:24.580 --> 01:17:25.570
作者亚历山大……
By Alexandree...

01:17:26.050 --> 01:17:27.310
大种马
Dum-ass.

01:17:27.650 --> 01:17:28.680
种马？
Dumb ass.

01:17:30.990 --> 01:17:32.050
种马？
Dumb ass?

01:17:34.960 --> 01:17:36.930
大仲马  内容知道吗？
Dumas. Know what that's about?

01:17:39.200 --> 01:17:41.170
讲逃狱  你会喜欢的
You'd like it. It's about a prison break.

01:17:41.370 --> 01:17:45.270
那该归入教育类啰
We ought to file that under "Educational" too, oughtn't we?

01:17:46.140 --> 01:17:50.230
大伙儿尽可能地帮忙
The rest of us did our best to pitch in when and where we could.

01:17:50.810 --> 01:17:52.570
在肯尼迪遇刺那年
By the year Kennedy was shot...

01:17:52.810 --> 01:17:57.310
安迪把这间臭储藏室变成
Andy had transformed a storage room smelling of turpentine...

01:17:57.620 --> 01:18:00.710
新英格兰最棒的监狱图书馆
into the best prison library in New England...

01:18:01.420 --> 01:18:04.360
甚至有汉克·威廉斯精选集
complete with a fine selection of Hank Williams.

01:18:11.730 --> 01:18:13.660
就在同年
That was also when Warden Norton...

01:18:13.870 --> 01:18:16.800
典狱长实施著名的“外役”专案
instituted his famous "Inside Out" program.

01:18:17.270 --> 01:18:19.330
也许你曾在报上看过
You may remember reading about it.

01:18:19.570 --> 01:18:22.670
他上了各报和《展望杂志》
It made the papers and got his picture in Look magazine.

01:18:22.870 --> 01:18:24.170
这不是放任自由
It's no free ride...

01:18:24.380 --> 01:18:27.610
而是狱政的
but rather a genuine progressive advance...

01:18:27.810 --> 01:18:30.300
一大进步
in corrections and rehabilitation.

01:18:30.650 --> 01:18:33.170
本监获刑人在妥善监督下
Our inmates, properly supervised...

01:18:33.390 --> 01:18:36.010
将到狱外劳动
will be put to work outside these walls...

01:18:36.220 --> 01:18:39.320
从事各项公共事业
performing all manner of public service.

01:18:39.490 --> 01:18:42.290
他们将学到诚实劳动的价值
These men can learn the value...

01:18:42.490 --> 01:18:46.290
同时为社区提供服务
of an honest day's labor and provide a service to the community...

01:18:46.500 --> 01:18:51.200
对于纳税大众而言  也只花最少的代价
at a bare minimum of expense to Mr. And Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.

01:18:51.640 --> 01:18:53.970
当然  诺顿没向媒体说明
Of course he didn't tell the press...

01:18:54.170 --> 01:18:57.630
“最少代价”实在含糊不清
that "bare minimum of expense" is a fairly loose term.

01:18:57.840 --> 01:19:00.870
揩油的方法何止百种
There are 100 different ways to skim off the top.

01:19:01.080 --> 01:19:03.570
人力  物料  处处漏洞
Men, materials, you name it.

01:19:03.920 --> 01:19:06.820
天哪  油水超多
And oh, my Lord, how the money rolled in!

01:19:07.020 --> 01:19:09.540
你会害我倒闭的
At this rate, you'll put me out of business.

01:19:09.750 --> 01:19:14.190
靠这么多奴工  谁投标投得过你
With this pool of slave labor, you can underbid any contractor in town.

01:19:14.760 --> 01:19:17.730
我们在提供社区服务
We're providing a valuable community service.

01:19:17.930 --> 01:19:22.330
这是说词  我得养家
That's fine for the papers, but I've got a family to feed.

01:19:24.270 --> 01:19:25.790
老兄  咱们这么久的交情
We go back a long way.

01:19:27.110 --> 01:19:32.040
我需要包下这条公路  不然只好喝西北风了
I need this highway contract. I don't get it and I go under. That's a fact.

01:19:32.940 --> 01:19:34.740
这是我太太特地为你烤的派
You have some of this fine pie...

01:19:34.980 --> 01:19:38.310
请笑纳
my missus made for you. You think about that.

01:19:46.590 --> 01:19:49.290
别担心这项工程合约
I wouldn't worry too much about this contract.

01:19:49.530 --> 01:19:52.590
我已叫他们接别的项目了
I already got my boys committed elsewhere.

01:19:54.570 --> 01:19:57.630
帮我谢谢她的心意
You be sure and thank Maisie for this fine pie.

01:19:58.740 --> 01:20:00.900
在每一桩买卖背后
And behind every shady deal...

01:20:01.240 --> 01:20:03.870
在每一个黑钱底下
behind every dollar earned...

01:20:04.140 --> 01:20:07.200
都有安迪在  是他做的帐
there was Andy, keeping the books.

01:20:07.610 --> 01:20:08.870
有两笔要存入银行
Two deposits.

01:20:09.110 --> 01:20:13.240
照旧在夜间  存到缅因国际和新英格兰
Maine National and New England First. Night drops as always, sir.

01:20:43.450 --> 01:20:47.780
把东西拿去洗衣房  两套西装和杂物
Get my stuff to the laundry. Two suits for dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.

01:20:48.250 --> 01:20:51.780
-别浆太硬  否则有他们好看  -是  先生
If they over-starch my shirts again, they'll hear from me.

01:20:51.990 --> 01:20:53.320
我怎样？
How do I look?

01:20:54.360 --> 01:20:57.050
-很好  先生  -要去参加盛大的慈善宴会
-Very nice.  -Big charity to-do up Portland way.

01:20:57.050 --> 01:20:58.580
州长会到
Governor will be there.

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:01.490
剩下的给你吃
You want the rest of this?

01:21:02.800 --> 01:21:04.740
烤的难吃透顶
Woman can't bake worth shit.

01:21:05.970 --> 01:21:07.300
谢谢您  先生
Thank you, sir.

01:21:10.140 --> 01:21:13.370
我听说这种派他收过很多
He's got his fingers in a lot of pies, from what I hear.

01:21:13.580 --> 01:21:18.410
你听说的只是皮毛  他干的坏事你根本想不到  重重的回扣
He's got scams you haven't even dreamed of. Kickbacks on his kickbacks.

01:21:18.620 --> 01:21:20.980
黑钱如河般在他脚下流
A river of dirty money running through here.

01:21:21.190 --> 01:21:25.020
贪污这么多迟早会曝光
Sooner or later, he'll have to explain where it came from.

01:21:25.220 --> 01:21:26.990
因此才要用我
That's where I come in.

01:21:27.590 --> 01:21:29.890
我过滤黑钱  一一漂白
I channel it. Filter it. Funnel it.

01:21:30.100 --> 01:21:32.930
股票  证券  市政公债
Stocks, securities, tax-free municipals.

01:21:33.260 --> 01:21:36.790
我让脏钱流入市场  等它回流时……
I send it out into the real world, and when it comes back...

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:39.970
-干净的像处女？  -比那更干净
-Clean as a virgin's honeypot, huh?  -Cleaner.

01:21:40.570 --> 01:21:44.170
诺顿退休时  将是百万富翁
By the time Norton retires, I'll have made him a millionaire.

01:21:46.510 --> 01:21:50.850
若被逮到  他也会被关入肖申克
If they ever catch on, he'll wind up in here wearing a number himself.

01:21:51.120 --> 01:21:53.810
你对我这么没信心啊
I thought you had more faith in me than that.

01:21:54.020 --> 01:21:57.050
我知道你很能干  但总会有蛛丝马迹留下
I know you're good, but all that paper leaves a trail.

01:21:57.260 --> 01:22:00.660
万一调查局或国税局起疑
Now anybody gets curious, FBI, IRS...

01:22:00.860 --> 01:22:01.850
就完了
whatever.

01:22:02.290 --> 01:22:03.590
总有人要遭殃
It'll lead to somebody.

01:22:03.800 --> 01:22:07.660
没错  但不是我  更不是典狱长
Sure it is, but not to me, and certainly not to the warden.

01:22:12.040 --> 01:22:13.030
那是谁？
All right, who?

01:22:13.240 --> 01:22:14.830
兰道·史帝文
Randall Stevens.

01:22:15.310 --> 01:22:16.300
谁？
Who?

01:22:16.510 --> 01:22:18.500
隐名又隐形的合伙人
The "silent" silent partner.

01:22:18.710 --> 01:22:21.770
法官  要怪怪他  户头是他的
He's the guilty one, the man with the bank accounts.

01:22:21.980 --> 01:22:24.140
他是洗钱的起点
It's where the filtering process starts.

01:22:24.350 --> 01:22:27.220
出了差错  只追得到他
They trace anything, it'll just lead to him.

01:22:27.820 --> 01:22:29.050
但他是什么人？
But who is he?

01:22:29.250 --> 01:22:33.210
他是幻影  幽灵  兔子哈维的远房表亲
He's a phantom, an apparition. Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.

01:22:34.330 --> 01:22:35.490
他由我一手
I conjured him...

01:22:35.690 --> 01:22:37.060
凭空塑造
out of thin air.

01:22:37.860 --> 01:22:40.590
他不存在  除了在文件上
He doesn't exist, except on paper.

01:22:43.670 --> 01:22:46.030
哪有凭空造人的？
You can't just make a person up.

01:22:46.240 --> 01:22:49.330
利用制度的漏洞就行
Sure you can, if you know how the system works.

01:22:49.840 --> 01:22:52.670
靠写信能办成太多的事
It's amazing what you can accomplish by mail.

01:22:53.010 --> 01:22:55.640
史帝文有出生证明
Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate...

01:22:55.850 --> 01:22:57.970
有驾照  社会保险编号
driver's license, Social Security.

01:22:58.250 --> 01:22:59.240
你在逗我吧？
You're shitting me.

01:22:59.450 --> 01:23:02.820
就算抓到蛛丝马迹
If they trace any accounts, they'll wind up chasing...

01:23:03.020 --> 01:23:04.750
也等于捕风捉影
a figment of my imagination.

01:23:04.960 --> 01:23:06.950
真想不到
Well, I'll be damned!

01:23:08.290 --> 01:23:10.020
我有称赞过你吧？
Did I say you were good?

01:23:10.400 --> 01:23:12.020
你简直是大艺术家
Shit, you are Rembrandt.

01:23:12.760 --> 01:23:14.490
可笑的是
The funny thing is...

01:23:14.700 --> 01:23:18.800
